We need to clear the path for our veterans to transition their service in uniform to success in civilian life by prioritizing veteran employment and setting them up for success in the 21st century economy. #AmazonFutureofWork
There are many obstacles veterans face as they transition from military to civilian life, but finding a good-paying job that harnesses their skills should not be one of them. #AmazonFutureofWork
Armed with a unique skill set and experience, our veterans are natural leaders and assets to employers, whether in the private sector, the public sector, or the non-profit sector. #AmazonFutureofWork

Roughly 500 veterans return to civilian life every single day, continuing their commitment to service by giving back to our local communities, starting small businesses, getting involved in public service, and more. #AmazonFutureofWork

This is a commonsense measure that ensures transparency, accountability & justice. Taxpayers should not have to foot the bill for egregious acts made by Members of Congress and their staff. Enough is enough. https://gabbard.house.gov/news/press-releases/photos-video-rep-tulsi-gabbard-introduces-legislation-empower-survivors-and-hold …pic.twitter.com/UxmDxmGsQ0

This is a commonsense measure that ensures transparency, accountability & justice. Taxpayers should not have to foot the bill for egregious acts made by Members of Congress and their staff. Enough is enough.
It also protects taxpayers by ending taxpayer-funded sexual #harassment settlements, and requiring reimbursement of previous taxpayer-funded settlements.

Our bipartisan legislation will empower survivors by increasing transparency and accountability, and providing survivors the freedom to publicly share their stories if they so choose, regardless of the non-disclosure agreements they were forced to sign.

That’s why I’m co-leading a bipartisan effort w/ @RepDeSantis, @RepKathleenRice, @MarshaBlackburn, and @repjimcooper & introduced the Congressional Accountability and Hush Fund Elimination Act to overhaul Congress’s sexual #harassment and assault policies https://gabbard.house.gov/news/press-releases/photos-video-rep-tulsi-gabbard-introduces-legislation-empower-survivors-and-hold …

The bottom line is clear: no one, whether it be a Capitol Hill staffer, Hollywood actor, schoolteacher, or soldier, or any other profession, should have to choose between their job and their personal safety

Survivors of sexual harassment and assault have been isolated, shamed, and bullied into silence, while their abusers walk away scot-free with the privilege of anonymity and without personal or financial accountability

This is wrong and must be corrected immediately. No more excuses. Members of Congress who harass their staffers must be held personally and financially responsible for their actions, and the public should be informed of their behavior.

Congress must take action now to address this pervasive problem. It is outrageous that hard-working American taxpayers have paid the bill for offending lawmakers’ harassment settlements totaling millions of dollars, while keeping the names of these predators secret.

No one, whether it be a Capitol Hill staffer, Hollywood actor, schoolteacher, or soldier, or any other profession, should have to choose between their job and their personal safety, security, and privacy.
For too long, victims of sexual assault and harassment have been shamed and bullied into silence, perpetuating an inexcusable culture that has no place in our country.

The FCC must fulfill their responsibility to all Americans, not just big ISPs. I urge the FCC to listen to the voices of more than 22 million public comments, including 61,707 from Hawai‘i, on #NetNeutrality and reject this corporate attack on equality

#NetNeutrality protections ensure that the Internet remains open, fair, and equal for everyone. By dismantling these protections, we turn our backs on the most fundamental First Amendment rights of all who rely on an open Internet to level the playing field of opportunity
Yet again, Chairman Pai and the FCC are rewarding pay-to-play politics, ensuring that those with money have a seat at the table, and shutting everyone else out #NetNeutrality

Under this #TaxBill corporate tax cuts are made permanent, while individual tax cuts are temporary, with many middle class families seeing their taxes increase in 10 years.

#Hawaii public school teachers spend hundreds of dollars of their own money every year buying supplies for their students. The #TaxBill passed today gets rid of the deduction they currently have to help with these out of pocket expenses, further driving down their take home pay

House-passed #TaxBill would strip clean energy incentives driving innovation in the Aloha State & nationwide, while maintaining over $14 billion in federal subsidies for the fossil fuel industry. This is exactly the wrong direction for our country

Deductions for major medical expenses, affecting roughly 33,000 people in #Hawaii are eliminated from the #TaxBill, creating a disproportionate impact on our kupuna and those most vulnerable already struggling to pay for the skyrocketing cost of medical care
Under GOP #TaxBill, over 45,000 #Hawaii students would lose the deductions they can take for student loan interest rates, burying them deeper into debt

Almost everyone can agree that we desperately need tax reform, but the #TaxBill passed by the House today is not the way to achieve it. I voted against this bill, which provides a windfall for corporate interests, leaving behind everyone else
